    <!-- CONTEXT -->
    <div class="case-section reveal">
      <div class="section-label">01 ¬∑ Context & Problem</div>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <h2>Not just a scraper.<br>A data system.</h2>
          <p>When I joined Roamlii, the brief sounded simple: "build a reliable scraper for tourism and event data." In reality, the problem was architectural. Each of 60+ source websites had different layouts, different bot rules, and different data quality. The team needed not just scripts but a coherent system ‚Äî source verification, extraction logic, error handling, and a reliable path from raw HTML to structured analytics tables.</p>
          <p>I took a lead role as a hands-on builder. Over 12 weeks, I evolved the project from "how do we scrape these sites?" to "how do we run an automated, auditable data pipeline that produces reliable tourism intelligence?"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-box">
          <div class="mono" style="margin-bottom:1.2rem; color: var(--green);">Three-Path Extraction Strategy</div>
          <div class="pipeline">
            <div class="pipeline-step">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Selector-Based Scraping</h4>
                <p>Preferred path. CSS selectors + requests + BeautifulSoup for static sites. Fast, cost-efficient.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pipeline-step">
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Dynamic Extraction (Crawl4AI ‚Üí Firecrawl)</h4>
                <p>Browser-based rendering for dynamic/JS-heavy sites. Pivoted from Crawl4AI to Firecrawl after performance testing proved scalability concerns.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pipeline-step">
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>LLM Fallback</h4>
                <p>For irregular, unstructured layouts where selectors and rendering both fail. Last resort with schema enforcement on output.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE -->
    <div class="case-section reveal">
      <div class="section-label">02 ¬∑ System Architecture</div>
      <h2>End-to-end on GCP.<br>Zero manual intervention.</h2>
      <p>The final system runs entirely on Google Cloud Platform. A Cloud Scheduler triggers Cloud Run Jobs every 3 days per category. Each job scrapes, validates, and writes structured JSONL to Cloud Storage. A BigQuery Data Transfer Service then loads to staging tables, scheduled MERGE queries deduplicate and promote to raw tables, and a unified view powers all dashboards.</p>

      <div class="pipeline" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Cloud Scheduler ‚Üí Cloud Run Jobs</h4>
            <p>Separate jobs for Events (fast + slow), Festivals, and Sports. Docker containerized. 1‚Äì2hr timeout per run. Triggered every 3 days at 2AM.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Cloud Storage (GCS)</h4>
            <p>Structured output folders per category/timestamp. JSONL records, CSV backups, site metrics, failure artifacts, and run_report.json as the completion signal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Cloud Functions (Event-Driven)</h4>
            <p>Triggered on run_report.json creation in GCS. Initiates BigQuery DTS load with distributed locking to prevent duplicate processing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>BigQuery ‚Äî Stage ‚Üí Raw ‚Üí Unified View</h4>
            <p>DTS APPENDS to staging tables. Scheduled MERGE queries deduplicate and upsert to raw tables partitioned by run_date, clustered by province and site_name. UNION ALL unified view content_raw_all powers all reporting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Looker Studio + Power BI</h4>
            <p>Real-time dashboards showing provincial coverage, city rankings, field completeness scores, and lead intelligence ‚Äî directly querying the unified BigQuery view.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CHALLENGES -->
    <div class="case-section reveal">
      <div class="section-label">03 ¬∑ Key Engineering Decisions</div>
      <h2>Problems I solved.</h2>
      <div class="cs-grid">
        <div class="cs-card challenge">
          <span class="cs-label">Challenge</span>
          <h4>Crawl4AI didn't scale</h4>
          <p>Slow render times, timeout issues, high credit consumption and variable output quality across 60+ sites made it unsustainable for multi-site, daily pipeline runs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card solution">
          <span class="cs-label">Solution</span>
          <h4>Evidence-based pivot to Firecrawl</h4>
          <p>Benchmarked both tools rigorously and presented data to the CEO. Firecrawl's caching, reliable navigation, and structured JSON support unlocked near-production stability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card challenge">
          <span class="cs-label">Challenge</span>
          <h4>Multiple micro-services = deployment hell</h4>
          <p>The original multi-service FastAPI + Redis + adapter stack was complex to maintain, slow to debug, and difficult to scale across new event categories.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card solution">
          <span class="cs-label">Solution</span>
          <h4>Single-runner Docker architecture</h4>
          <p>Merged all services into one binary, one Docker image, one Cloud Run Job per category. Dramatically simplified deployment while enabling category-level targeting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card challenge">
          <span class="cs-label">Challenge</span>
          <h4>Duplicate records from multiple sources</h4>
          <p>60+ sites covering overlapping geographies created significant duplication in raw data, corrupting dashboard metrics and inflating event counts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card solution">
          <span class="cs-label">Solution</span>
          <h4>MERGE + partitioning + clustering</h4>
          <p>Implemented MERGE INTO logic keeping newest values, partitioned by run_date, clustered by province and site_name. Dramatically improved query performance and data accuracy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card challenge">
          <span class="cs-label">Challenge</span>
          <h4>Events missing dates in dashboards</h4>
          <p>Many listings stored dates as time_slots rather than explicit start/end dates, causing Looker Studio and Power BI to render broken timelines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-card solution">
          <span class="cs-label">Solution</span>
          <h4>SQL transformation for temporal normalization</h4>
          <p>Wrote a SQL transformation that parsed time_slots fields into explicit start_date and end_date regardless of source format, fixing timelines and improving lead scoring accuracy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RESULTS -->
    <div class="case-section reveal">
      <div class="section-label">04 ¬∑ Analytics Outputs & Results</div>
      <h2>Real intelligence.<br>Real business value.</h2>
      <p>By Week 12, the pipeline was operating end-to-end with zero manual intervention. The Looker Studio dashboard delivered nationwide tourism coverage with lead intelligence that directly feeds Roamlii's business development pipeline.</p>

      <div class="metrics-grid">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val">1,163</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">Total Events Discovered</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val">728</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">High-Value Leads Identified</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val">35.4%</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">Contactable Lead Rate</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val">55.8%</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">Avg Field Completeness Score</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val yellow">280</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">Quebec Events (Top Province)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-val yellow">162</span>
          <span class="metric-desc">Montr√©al (Top City)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="impact-list" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <li><span class="impact-icon">‚Üó</span> Fully automated scraping ‚Üí GCS ‚Üí BigQuery pipeline ‚Äî no manual steps from trigger to dashboard</li>
        <li><span class="impact-icon">‚Üó</span> 98% extraction accuracy achieved through modular Python adapters with strict schema validation</li>
        <li><span class="impact-icon">‚Üó</span> Nationwide coverage across all Canadian provinces ‚Äî Quebec, Ontario, Alberta, BC and beyond</li>
        <li><span class="impact-icon">‚Üó</span> 85 contacts already made by Roamlii's business team using lead intelligence from the pipeline</li>
        <li><span class="impact-icon">‚Üó</span> Distributed locking + resume logic = pipeline reliability at scale with zero data duplication</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

